Manchester United welcome rivals Manchester City in the first leg of their Carabao Cup semi-final on Tuesday night. United took all three points, when both sides met in the Premier League last month at the Etihad. However, Pep Guardiola will be seeking to retain the title he won last season, especially with the chances of winning the league almost gone. Kick off is 9pm West African time. Man United XI vs Man City: De Gea, Wan-Bissaka, Jones, Lindelof, Williams, Fred, Andreas, James, Lingard, Rashford, Greenwood Man City XI vs Man United: Bravo, Walker, Otamendi, Fernandinho, Mendy, Rodrigo, Gundogan, Mahrez, De Bruyne, Bernardo, Sterling Tuesday, January 7
